USE & CARE Stay away from metal utensil in cooking as well as steel wools in cleaning. 1.When preheating the pan, it's best not to preheat for too long, as the pan can become too hot and cause the eggs to stick. 2.Use an adequate amount of oil on the flat pan. 3.When frying eggs, it's advisable to use medium to low heat. Stainless steel has fast heat conductivity, and using medium to low heat will produce similar heat levels to what you'd get with aluminum cookware on high heat. 4.Recommend hand washing for longer term use. Suitable for dishwasher.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Well made, non-stick pan
reviews.reviewText: I'm really liking this pan! Well made and it cooks everything wonderfully and also a breeze to clean. Great for making eggs or an omelet, it distributes heat uniformly and nothing sticks to it. I bought the 10" and I'm probably going to get the 12" too.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 6, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I like this nonstick pan overall because it is easy to use, not heavy, and seems sturdy. The only downside is that sometimes when I don't cook at a high-enough temperature or put butter/oil on the pan before cooking, it could get stuck on the surface and I have to put extra care in rubbing those off from each crevice. But it barely sticks, to begin with. So I am enjoying using this pan. It's also really nice that it does not have any rivets!! I hope it's sturdy, which so far I've observed as sturdy and well-made. I also love how it's actually genuinely dishwasher safe, without producing any dripping rust water or showing spots of rush, say, on the bottom like some other products.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewText: As a Registered Dietitian who cooks everyday. This by far is the best skillet I have ever used, it hears up evenly and quickly. It has an amazing texture that doesn't allow food to stick. And it cleans so easily. I would recommend this skillet to anyone who cooks.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Good quality pan so far. Sometimes the food appears to stick after cooking, however, it wipes up pretty well with soap and sponge. I took off 1 star because after first use, the rim of the pan turned brown. I had to use a Brillo pad to remove the stains, only around the rim though as not to damage the non stick surface.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This skillet does its job very well, is easy to clean, and nothing sticks!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good quality pan
reviews.reviewText: This is such a nice pan! Great quality and heat is distributed evenly throughout. Super easy to clean with just dish soap and water. Seasoned after I received it so foods wouldn't stick. Would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 10, 2024
reviews.reviewText: We bought this “Aceself” pan because it looks just like a certain very expensive, heavily marketed pan with a British accent. Husband and I have been using it for a couple of weeks. I’ve fried eggs, scrambled eggs and sausage, cooked chicken, steak, and burgers with it. It will not scratch and washes easily. Not sure what else I’d want a pan to do. I guess we haven’t put it in the oven yet. It’s a good pan and I’m glad we didn’t spend one kazillion dollars to get the one that yells a lot. :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Good enough pan
reviews.reviewText: The pan is ok. Not bad but just OK. Used it a few times and eggs and other foods have already started sticking. The handle is wobbly. But I still use it to heat up or make simple foods.
